{"id": "1441275703352885380", "channel_id": "1441275703352885380", "type": 0, "author_id": "455376494034812948", "author_name": "reverie.is.dead", "author_bot": false, "content": "I encountered an unexpected behaviour: \n1. Silver Relic \"☆Withered Pupil☆\" was used on Murphy's 3 cost Vortex Reversal card, permanently changing it to 1 cost.\n2. During battle, Tawil's Omniscient Verity becomes a copy of Vortex Reversal with **2 cost**, ignoring the relic and instead applying the -1 cost discount to the original 3 cost Vortex Reversal. \n\nIn the draw pile, Vortex Reversal is shown with 1 cost. When the top card is drawn, it is Vortex Reversal with 1 cost. So I expected that when copying the card in my deck, Omniscient Verity would become 1 -1 = 0 cost Vortex Reversal.\n\nIs this intended— Omniscient Verity references the original form of the copied card and ignores relic effects— or is it bug?", "timestamp": "2025-11-21T03:55:05.287000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1441275703352885380", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "💭「Processing」Omniscient Verity and Withered Pupil Relic", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "is_thread_starter": true, "thread_tags": ["1361168893200044183"]}
